article.headline: Wis.-Green Bay 82, N. Illinois 76
article.story: DEKALB, Ill. (AP) -- Mike Schachtner scored 25 points Saturday to lead Wisconsin-Green Bay to an 82-76 win over Northern Illinois. The Phoenix (16-12) led 41-38 at halftime and never trailed during the second half, although Northern Illinois kept things close until the final minutes. James Hughes made two free throws to pull the Huskies to within 67-64 with 3:53 remaining. But Wisconsin-Green Bay scored the next eight points, keyed by a Ryan Tillema 3-pointer and a jumper from Schachtner, to pull out of the reach of Northern Illinois. Tillema scored 17 points for the Phoenix while never attempting a field goal inside the 3-point line. He went 4-of-7 from beyond the arc. Ryan Evanochko added 17 points for Wisconsin-Green Bay. Zach Pancratz scored 22 points to lead Northern Illinois (6-19), with Hughes adding 19. Northern Illinois outscored the Phoenix in the paint 32-20, but Wisconsin-Green Bay scored 20 points off 12 Huskie turnovers, while committing just six turnovers of their own.
